You are building Phase 11 of the Yuni dating app. Read CLAUDE.md for full project context. Phases 0-10 are complete.

Build the admin dashboard API ‚Äî consolidated admin endpoints for user management, manual matching, and analytics.

## 1. backend/app/schemas/admin.py

- `AdminUserListResponse`: list of users with id, email, first_name, last_name, gender, age, is_email_verified, is_selfie_verified, is_suspended, no_show_count, created_at, total_groups, total_matches
- `AdminUserDetailResponse`: full user info + list of groups, matches, reports (both filed and received)
- `ManualGroupCreate`: user_ids (list[UUID], 4 or 6), activity (str), scheduled_date (date), scheduled_time (str)
- `AnalyticsResponse`: total_users, active_users (created request in last 30 days), total_groups, total_matches, avg_experience_rating, total_reports_pending, no_show_count_total

## 2. backend/app/routers/admin.py

Prefix: `/api/admin`. All endpoints require admin auth.

- `GET /api/admin/users` ‚Äî List users with pagination and search. Query params: search (searches email/name), gender, is_suspended, limit (default 20), offset (default 0).
- `GET /api/admin/users/{user_id}` ‚Äî Get detailed user info including their groups, matches, and reports.
- `PATCH /api/admin/users/{user_id}` ‚Äî Suspend/unsuspend, set is_admin. Body: is_suspended (optional bool), is_admin (optional bool).
- `GET /api/admin/date-requests/pending` ‚Äî List all pending date requests with user info. This is what admins see when doing manual matching.
- `POST /api/admin/matching/manual` ‚Äî Manually create a group from selected users.
  - Validate: correct count (4 or 6), equal gender split
  - Create DateGroup, GroupMember records
  - Update DateRequests to status="matched"
  - Create group ChatRoom + participants
  - Return the created group
- `GET /api/admin/analytics` ‚Äî Return AnalyticsResponse with aggregated stats.

Note: POST /api/admin/matching/run-batch and report endpoints already exist from previous phases. This phase adds the user management and manual matching endpoints.

## 3. Update backend/app/main.py

Include the admin router (make sure it doesn't conflict with existing admin endpoints from matching and reports routers).

## 4. backend/tests/test_admin.py

1. `test_admin_list_users` ‚Äî admin can list users with pagination
2. `test_admin_search_users` ‚Äî search by name returns matching users
3. `test_admin_user_detail` ‚Äî admin gets detailed user info
4. `test_non_admin_rejected` ‚Äî non-admin gets 403 on all admin endpoints
5. `test_admin_suspend_user` ‚Äî admin suspends a user, verify is_suspended=True
6. `test_admin_unsuspend_user` ‚Äî admin unsuspends, verify is_suspended=False
7. `test_admin_manual_group` ‚Äî admin creates a group from 4 users (2M+2F), verify group created with chat room
8. `test_admin_manual_group_wrong_gender_split` ‚Äî 3M+1F, expect 400
9. `test_admin_pending_requests` ‚Äî create pending requests, admin endpoint returns them
10. `test_admin_analytics` ‚Äî verify analytics endpoint returns correct counts

IMPORTANT:
- Manual matching is the PRIMARY matching method for MVP. Make the UI-facing data as useful as possible.
- The pending requests endpoint should include user profile info so admins can make informed decisions.
- Analytics queries should be efficient (use COUNT, AVG aggregates, not loading all records)
